%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6849f294f748d8c055f38661%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221552%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20screenshot%20of%20the%20temporarily-removed%202nd%20Battalion%2C%207th%20Marine%20Regiment%20website%2C%2011%20June%2C%202025.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%26quot%3Bcommand%20duty%20officer%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20service%20member%20appointed%20to%20stand%20watch%20over%20a%20unit%20for%20a%2024-hour%20period.%20Such%20postings%20are%20routine%20for%20leaders%20and%20can%20quickly%20become%20critical.%20The%20phone%20line%20is%20often%20the%20first%20to%20receive%20urgent%20news%20regarding%20unit%20member%20emergencies%2C%20meaning%20that%20prank%20calls%20to%20such%20numbers%20could%20stop%20information%20from%20reaching%20those%20in%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20extended%20to%20Marines'%20families%2C%20contributing%20to%20the%20decision%20to%20remove%20the%20website.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20the%20mission%20is%20complete%20and%20the%20Marines%20safely%20return%20home%2C%20we%20will%20immediately%20restore%20the%20website%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20done%20trying%20to%20protect%20members%20of%20the%20unit%20from%20being%20doxxed%20or%20harassed%2C%26quot%3B%20Burke%20said%20on%20a%20phone%20call%2C%20explaining%20that%20the%20website's%20removal%20was%20only%20temporary%20and%20done%20out%20of%20safety%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aaa719cb-dfb5-4e98-b57e-029ccb4cd55f%5C%22%3EThe%20growing%20civil-military%20divide%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20unease%20is%20uncommon%20for%20active-duty%20units%2C%20often%20too%20busy%20with%20training%20to%20rile%20up%20such%20sentiments.%20The%20military%20has%20enjoyed%20high%20public%20trust%20for%20decades%2C%20though%20research%20indicates%20such%20trust%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmwi.westpoint.edu%2Fclosing-the-us-militarys-public-trust-deficit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20waned%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20becoming%20increasingly%20fragile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutsiders%20harassing%20military%20personnel%20could%20be%20symptomatic%20of%20the%20growing%20civil-military%20divide%2C%20the%20growing%20chasm%20between%20those%20who%20serve%20and%20those%20who%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMembers%20of%20the%20armed%20forces%20are%20often%2C%20though%20not%20always%2C%20confined%20to%20remote%20bases%20like%20Twentynine%20Palms%2C%20California%2C%20over%20two%20hours%20east%20of%20Los%20Angeles.%20Military%20recruitment%20continues%20to%20rely%20heavily%20on%20families%20who%20already%20have%20histories%20of%20service%2C%20and%20the%20US%20veteran%20population%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F11%2F08%2Fthe-changing-face-of-americas-veteran-population%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20decline%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20Americans%20may%20only%20see%20uniformed%20service%20members%20at%20airports%2C%20fostering%20fundamental%20misunderstandings%20about%20the%20people%20who%20serve%20and%20who%20is%20calling%20the%20shots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProtestors%20met%20Marines%20departing%20their%20base%20and%20arriving%20at%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20despite%20the%20Marine%20leaders%20having%20little%20choice%20in%20the%20matter.%20Missions%2C%20normally%20coordinated%20with%20state%20and%20local%20leaders%2C%20originate%20from%20much%20higher%20levels%20%E2%80%94%20in%20this%20case%2C%20from%20the%20Secretary%20of%20Defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarine-unit-la-took-website-down-dodge-prank-calls-harassment-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749677727000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6849f63c85e81483682bed58%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarine-uni