nte%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F361124%2Frammed-earth-timber-clay-sustainable-home-material-architecture-projects-in-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ensive%20pro%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F361124%2Frammed-earth-timber-clay-sustainable-home-material-architecture-projects-in-india%2F%5C%22%3Eduction%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20concrete%2C%20Krithika%20points%20out%20its%20relatively%20short%20lifespan%20and%20the%20health%20hazards%20associated%20with%20modern%20concrete%20and%20its%20finishes.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20cement%20concrete%2C%20follows%20plaster%20and%20heavy%2C%20toxic%20paints%20on%20top%20of%20these%20layers%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrithika%20also%20worked%20on%20a%20study%20along%20with%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20Madras%20in%202020%20to%20measure%20the%20indoor%20air%20quality%20index%20for%20Chennai%20households.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20we%20found%20that%20apartments%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20VOCs%20(Volatile%20Organic%20Compounds).%20We%20found%20the%20air%20quality%20index%20was%20so%20bad%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20outdoors%2C%20contributing%20to%20%E2%80%98sick%20building%20syndrome%E2%80%99%20as%20recognised%20by%20the%20WHO%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBreathing%20walls%20and%20earthy%20floors%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20antidote%3F%20For%20Krithika%20and%20her%20team%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20return%20to%20the%20wisdom%20of%20traditional%20building%20practices%2C%20using%20materials%20that%20are%20kind%20to%20the%20earth%20and%20to%20the%20people%20who%20inhabit%20the%20structures.%20Her%20approach%20to%20building%20emphasises%20the%20use%20of%20natural%20and%20locally%20sourced%20materials%20and%20we%20have%20broken%20it%20down%20for%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20was%20such%20that%20not%20only%20did%20it%20give%20people%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F419684%2Fsustainable-architecture-in-india-using-stone-lime-moss-the-timber-residence-vagator%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthier%20option%20to%20live%20%3C%2Fa%3Ebut%20also%20the%20force%20that%20was%20working%20with%20these%20natural%20materials%20saw%20a%20betterment%20in%20their%20health.%20%E2%80%9CA%20few%20of%20my%20painters%20who%20do%20lime%20wash%20and%20lime%20plastic%20have%20told%20me%20that%20since%20they%20started%20working%20with%20natural%20substances%2C%20they%20did%20not%20encounter%20a%20problem%20of%20sinus%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares%20with%20a%20smile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhanajayan%20(52)%2C%20who%20has%20been%20a%20mason%20since%20he%20was%2015%20years%20old%2C%20shares%20that%20he%20enjoys%20working%20for%20sustainable%20buildings.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20always%20been%20interested%20in%20lime%20buildings%20since%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20involved%20in%20constructing%20buildings%20using%20traditional%20and%20old%20methods%20that%20eliminate%20concrete%20or%20cement%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHappy%20clients%2C%20happy%20planet%3A%20A%20win-win%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWord%20of%20Krithika%E2%80%99s%20unique%20approach%20has%20spread%2C%20and%20her%20clients%20are%20enamoured%20with%20the%20results.%20%E2%80%9CSlowly%2C%20by%20word%20of%20mouth%2C%20I%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20projects%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Krithika.%20They%20appreciate%20not%20just%20the%20aesthetic%20charm%20and%20the%20connection%20to%20nature%2C%20but%20also%20the%20holistic%20approach%20that%20considers%20everything%20from%20water%20management%20to%20the%20very%20air%20they%20breathe%20indoors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishna%20Subramanian%2C%20a%20satisfied%20client%20of%20Studio%20for%20Earthen%20Architecture%2C%20shares%20his%20experience%20of%20constructing%20an%20eco-fr